HEADWORD: Icelandic
<hw>Ice*lan"dic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to Iceland; relating to, or resembling, the Icelanders.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Icelandic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Icelandic
<hw>Ice*lan"dic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The language of
the Icelanders. It is one of the Scandinavian group, and is more nearly
allied to the Old Norse than any other language now spoken.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iceland moss</ent>⟦br⟧
